(8, 0, 9, 0, 'dyt-magnetic-workholding', 'DYT magnetic workholding', '', 'news_pic1593701025515.jpg', '', '<ul class=\"move-ul \"><li style=\"font-size: 0;\"><div class=\"imageContainer ne\" style=\"width:100%;display: inline-block; padding:10px; font-size:14px;vertical-align: top;\"><p><br>\n\n<span>Multi-functional permanent magnetic workholding is a new concept of clamping.<br><br>\n\nIt can be used separately, or conbine severel together for lifting more biger workpiece.<br><br>\n\nPatent No:200820043478.2<br><br></span>\n</p><p class=\"pro_det_img\"><img src=\"../upfiles/pic1592294969604.jpg\"></p> \n<p></p></div></li>\r\n	</ul>', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '', '', '', ''),
(9, 0, 9, 0, 'neodymium-magnet', 'Neodymium magnet', '', 'news_pic1593701487873.jpg', '', '<ul class=\"move-ul \"><li style=\"font-size: 0;\"><div class=\"imageContainer ne\" style=\"width:100%;display: inline-block; padding:10px; font-size:14px;vertical-align: top;\"><p><br>\n\n<span>A neodymium magnet (also known as NdFeB, NIB, or Neo magnet), the most widely-used type of rare-earth magnet, is a permanent magnet made from an alloy of neodymium, iron, and boron to form the Nd2Fe14B tetragonal crystalline structure. Developed in 1982 by General Motors and Sumitomo Special Metals, neodymium magnets are the strongest type of permanent magnet made. They have replaced other types of magnet in the many applications in modern products that require strong permanent magnets, such as motors in cordless tools, hard disk drives, and magnetic fasteners.<br><br></span>\n</p><p class=\"pro_det_img\"><img src=\"../upfiles/pic1592818500279.jpg\"></p> \n<p></p></div></li>\r\n	</ul>', '2007-04-25 16:00:00', 0, 0, '', '', '', ''),
